dc_title_s: Carte geologique detaillee de la France [a 1/80 000]: Sarrebourg
dc_description_s: France. Service de la carte geologique de France Explanatory text: 1 sheet in MC folder. North Decimal Degree 49.0757 South Decimal Degree 48.7163 East Decimal Degree 7.1564 West Decimal Degree 6.2819 Relief shown by hachures. Principal meridian: Paris. Longitude is given in centesimal values (100 grades = 90 degrees) .The Service de la carte geologique de la France was integrated to the BRGM to become the only France Service geologique national. Based on "Carte topograqphique de l'etat major."
